      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "bash"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Use gVisor as the Docker runtime (requires runsc installed)\n# /etc/docker/daemon.json\n{\n  \"runtimes\": {\n    \"runsc\": {\n      \"path\": \"/usr/local/bin/runsc\"\n    }\n  }\n}\n\n# Run a container with gVisor\ndocker run --runtime=runsc --rm \\\n  --network none \\\n  --memory 128m \\\n  python:3.12-slim \\\n  python3 -c \"print('hello from gVisor')\" "
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Cloud Sandbox APIs"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Managed sandbox APIs handle the infrastructure so you do not have to operate containers yourself. E2B, Modal, and similar services provide ephemeral VMs or containers with a simple API:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# E2B \u2014 managed Firecracker microVM sandboxes\n# pip install e2b-code-interpreter\n\nimport os\nfrom e2b_code_interpreter import Sandbox\n\ndef run_in_e2b(code: str) -> dict:\n    with Sandbox(api_key=os.environ[\"E2B_API_KEY\"]) as sbx:\n        execution = sbx.run_code(code)\n        return {\n            \"stdout\": \"\\n\".join(str(r) for r in execution.logs.stdout),\n            \"stderr\": \"\\n\".join(str(r) for r in execution.logs.stderr),\n            \"error\": str(execution.error) if execution.error else None,\n        }\n\n# Modal \u2014 serverless containers with GPU support\n# pip install modal\nimport modal\n\napp = modal.App(\"code-sandbox\")\nimage = modal.Image.debian_slim().pip_install(\"numpy\", \"pandas\", \"matplotlib\")\n\n@app.function(image=image, timeout=30, memory=512)\ndef run_code(code: str) -> dict:\n    import subprocess, sys\n    proc = subprocess.run(\n        [sys.executable, \"-c\", code],\n        capture_output=True, text=True, timeout=25\n    )\n    return {\"stdout\": proc.stdout[:8192], \"stderr\": proc.stderr[:2048]}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Stateful vs Stateless Sandboxes"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A stateless sandbox starts fresh on every call \u2014 the filesystem, installed packages, and in-memory state are discarded. A stateful sandbox persists between calls, allowing the agent to install packages once and accumulate results across multiple tool invocations:"
          }
        ]
      },
