      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Sandbox environments exist on a spectrum from lightweight subprocess isolation (fast, weak) to hardware-level VM boundaries (slower, strongest). The choice depends on the trust level of the code source and the sensitivity of the host: subprocess for trusted operators, Docker for internal agents, gVisor or Firecracker for public-facing multi-tenant services. Stateful sandboxes persist state across calls for REPL-style agents; stateless sandboxes reset on every invocation, eliminating cross-call data leakage."
